## Appendix A — Aspirational “Block 5”: maximum telemetry (not in repo)

The following was proposed for a **bristling ball of semi-live telemetry** on Quest. **None of this is implemented** unless files appear under `Assets/Chorewars/Scripts/Diagnostics/`. Use it to plan features and PR breakdowns; do not assume it exists in builds.

**Principles (aspirational):**

- Diagnostic Mode with labelled **Continue** steps before full startup.  
- **Telemetry HUD** in-headset (subsystem status, FPS, memory, last N log lines).  
- **Structured JSON line logging** to `Application.persistentDataPath` (e.g. `MQ3.log`) with rotation ~10 MB.  
- **SubsystemHealth** model (enum per subsystem: NotStarted, Initialising, Ok, Failed).  
- **Fail loudly:** exceptions → logger + HUD + health state.  

**Suggested deliverables (when implemented):**

| File (proposed) | Role |
|-----------------|------|
| `Assets/Chorewars/Scripts/Diagnostics/DiagnosticManager.cs` | Step gating, default diagnostic mode on until stable. |
| `Assets/Chorewars/Scripts/Diagnostics/TelemetryHUD.cs` | In-headset status + metrics. |
| `Assets/Chorewars/Scripts/Diagnostics/TelemetryLogger.cs` | JSON lines, rotation, `Info/Warn/Error` API. |
| `Assets/Chorewars/Scripts/Diagnostics/SubsystemHealth.cs` | Single source of truth for HUD. |
| `Assets/Chorewars/Prefabs/DiagnosticCanvas.prefab` | World-space or overlay UI. |

**Step sequence (proposed):** (1) Scene loaded (2) XR loader (3) Passthrough permission (4) Passthrough started (5) AR camera (6) HUD (7) Mode controller (8) Path tracker (9) Coverage map (10) Enter game.

**Definition of done (for a future PR):** On device in diagnostic mode, user sees stepper + HUD + disk log; failures are visible in all three.  

Document pull paths for `MQ3.log` via `adb` in `README` or `docs/` when this ships.

